## Operator Breakdown
- **σ (Air/Aerunik — Distinction)**: extended|bounded — The fundamental distinction between mind as extending beyond the brain into fields of influence and mind as confined to the physical brain, challenging the materialist paradigm at its foundation
- **ρ (Water/Sentaria — Relation)**: field|isolation — Morphic fields create relational connections between organisms across space and time, contrasted with the materialist view of isolated neural systems. Evidence includes telephone telepathy, sensation of being watched, and premonitions
- **λ (Fire/Jvalion — Transformation)**: resonance|decay — Morphic resonance as the mechanism by which patterns are transmitted and reinforced across time and space, transforming how development and behavior unfold through non-local influence
- **β (Wood/Arboriel — Growth)**: habit|novelty — Morphic fields grow stronger through repetition, establishing habits at biological and behavioral levels. Each repetition deepens the morphic groove, making patterns increasingly probable over time
- **δγ (Earth/Humavita — Cycling)**: memory|forgetting — The cycling of morphic memory across generations, where developmental blueprints recur and are refreshed through each instantiation, creating a cumulative memory that transcends individual organisms
- **μ (Metal/Ferrosid — Structure)**: morphic|material — The structural architecture of morphic fields as invisible blueprints that guide development and behavior, contrasted with material structures favored by conventional science

